{comment: Verse 1}
Well, it's a [Am]marvelous [Bm/A]night for a [Am7]moondance
    [D/A]With the [Am]stars up [Bm/A]above in your [Am7]eyes[D/A]
A [Am]fantabulous [Bm/A]night to make [Am7]romance
    [D/A]'Neath the [Am]colour of [Bm/A]October [Am7]skies[D/A]
And all the [Am]leaves on the [Bm/A]trees are [Am7]falling
    [D/A]To the [Am]sound of the [Bm/A]breezes that [Am7]blow[D/A]
And I'm [Am]trying to [Bm/A]please to the [Am7]calling
    [D/A]Of your [Am]heartstrings that [Bm/A]play soft and [Am7]low[D/A]

{comment: Pre-Chorus 1}
You know the [Dm]night's [Am]magic
Seems to [Dm]whisper and [Am]hush
You know the [Dm]soft [Am]moonlight
Seems to shine[Dm]
In your blush[E7]

{comment: Chorus 1}
